						<summary>

						<p>Two pieces of a slab lying at the entrance of the office of the Asst. Engineer.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Trailōkyamalla [Sōmēśvara I] 11th century A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This highly damaged record refers to the rule of Chālukya Trailōkyamalla, to an officer (probably [chā]kaya) administering Kisukāḍu-70 division and to <hi rend="italic">mahāsāmanta, manneya</hi> Dojjarasa [Ajjarasa]. It records gift of land, houses, oil-mill etc., to a deity and for feeding ascetics.</p>						

						<p>The record is dated 9 • • • • • Mārggaśira, śu. 5, <hi rend="italic">uttarāyaṇa (saṁkrānti).</hi> The information is insufficient for verification. The record is in the characters of the 11th century A.D.</p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
